  "instructions": [
    "1. Preheat grill to medium-high heat.",
    "2. Season the beef with salt and black pepper.",
    "3. Grill the beef for 3-4 minutes per side, or until cooked to your desired level of doneness.",
    "4. Meanwhile, heat the coconut water in a saucepan over medium heat.",
    "5. Add the fish sauce and bring to a simmer.",
    "6. Stir in the chopped scallions.",
    "7. To assemble the com tam, place a scoop of crispy rice on a plate, followed by a slice of grilled beef.",
    "8. Spoon some of the fish sauce mixture over the beef, and top with a sprinkle of tam huu.",
    "9. Serve immediately and garnish with lime wedges.",
    "10. Enjoy!"
